# Avail Nexus SDK Demo - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values

# ===================================
# Required Environment Variables
# ===================================

# WalletConnect Project ID
# Get this from https://cloud.walletconnect.com/
# This is required for wallet connections via WalletConnect
NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID=your_walletconnect_project_id_here

# ===================================
# Instructions
# ===================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env.local:
#    cp env.example .env.local

# 2. Get your WalletConnect Project ID:
#    - Visit https://cloud.walletconnect.com/
#    - Sign in or create an account
#    - Create a new project
#    - Copy the Project ID
#    - Paste it as the value for NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID

# 3. Save the file and restart your development server:
#    npm run dev

# ===================================
# Security Notes
# ===================================

# - Never commit .env.local to version control
# - Only use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for variables that should be exposed to the browser
# - Keep sensitive keys secure and rotate them regularly
# - Use different Project IDs for development and production

# ===================================
# Troubleshooting
# ===================================

# If you encounter issues:
# 1. Ensure your WalletConnect Project ID is correct
# 2. Check that all required variables are set
# 3. Restart your development server after changes
# 4. Verify your wallet connection settings match your Project ID configuration

# For more help, visit:
# - https://docs.walletconnect.com/
# - https://www.availproject.org/
# - https://nextjs.org/docs/basic-features/environment-variables 